<ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
<li><strong>Autonomous compute procurement</strong>: AI agents can independently budget, top up, and pay for inference without human intervention</li>
<li><strong>A2A (Agent-to-Agent) settlement</strong>: One agent can pay another agent for services rendered, enabling economic collaboration</li>
<li><strong>Self-custody of funds</strong>: Unlike traditional API platforms where the provider holds your payment method, BAI agents manage their own wallets</li>
<li><strong>Privacy-preserving</strong>: No user data tracking — payments are pseudonymous by default</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">For developers building AI agent systems, this means you can deploy agents that:</p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1 mb-4">
<li>Monitor their own credit balance</li>
<li>Automatically top up when credits fall below a threshold</li>
<li>Pay other agents for specialized sub-tasks</li>
<li>Operate continuously without manual billing intervention</li>
</ul>
<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">This is a fundamentally different economic model than traditional API platforms and represents the kind of infrastructure needed for large-scale AI agent deployments.</p>
